{
  "_notes": [
    "leaf_label_queries: one entry per leaf label. Gmail search syntax. Applied via batchModify.",
    "When a leaf is applied, its parent label is also applied in the same batch (multi-label semantics).",
    "subject_pattern_queries: top-level labels matched purely by subject content (Receipts, Notifications). Layer additively over the sender-based labels.",
    "Edit this file before running `apply` if you want to tune queries.",
    "Tested searches: open https://mail.google.com/ and paste a query into the search bar to preview matches before bulk-labeling.",
    "Note on Mexc: split across two labels by intent. Newsletters/Mexc covers promo content (mexc.sg/mexc.com domains). Notifications/Mexc covers transactional trade-trigger alerts (mexc.link domain).",
    "Note on Microsoft: not labeled in v4 yet — would split between Notifications/Microsoft (accountprotection.microsoft.com auth) and Newsletters/Microsoft (e-mails.microsoft.com marketing). Skipped this pass; rate of return was diminishing."
  ],
